[Groans] Kill me.

12:44.294 --> 12:46.495
Not you, Sid. It was just an expression.

12:46.496 --> 12:50.366
Another good one, sir.

12:50.367 --> 12:51.633
[Metal clashing]

12:58.908 --> 13:00.709
I'm ready to do whatever I need

13:00.710 --> 13:02.378
to join the dark, dark evil w...

13:02.379 --> 13:03.445
[gasps]

13:03.446 --> 13:05.014
Excellent.

13:05.015 --> 13:07.950
Oh, God, no, sorry.

13:07.951 --> 13:09.817
That's beyond even me.

13:11.288 --> 13:12.721
Oh, fine, give it here.

13:12.722 --> 13:14.023
No, no. It's all right.

13:14.024 --> 13:16.725
I'm just babysitting for
one of the kitchen staff.

13:16.726 --> 13:20.062
I was cutting up a peach
for the little chap.

13:20.063 --> 13:22.231
Oh, sorry, I thought you meant...

13:22.232 --> 13:23.966
Kcch!

13:23.967 --> 13:27.803
Ah, right, so, the
D'Dew. You're interested?

13:27.804 --> 13:30.105
Very. I'm in. Let's d'do it.

13:30.106 --> 13:32.107
Oh, God, that's very funny.

13:32.108 --> 13:34.343
[Laughs] Thank you.

13:34.344 --> 13:37.813
I think with these powers,
you'll definitely win the war.

13:37.814 --> 13:40.282
And I think you'll find the D'Dew folks

13:40.283 --> 13:42.885
a fun group of people to be with.

13:42.886 --> 13:44.653
So, is there like a ceremony or something?

13:44.654 --> 13:47.389
No, you just sign a contract
for your immortal soul.

13:47.391 --> 13:50.060
- Oh.
- Ah, where did I put it?

13:50.060 --> 13:53.062
Ahh.

13:53.063 --> 13:53.962
Here.

13:53.963 --> 13:55.130
If...

13:55.131 --> 13:56.465
[whimpers]

13:56.466 --> 13:59.034
No, no, no. You don't
have to sign in blood.

13:59.035 --> 14:00.969
Huh? I just gave you the knife to hold.

14:00.970 --> 14:02.504
A quill is fine.

14:02.505 --> 14:05.006
[Chuckles]

14:05.775 --> 14:09.143
Yes, but points for enthusiasm, though.

14:10.480 --> 14:13.282
If you could, let's just keep
this as our little secret.

14:13.283 --> 14:15.317
There's no reason Gareth needs to know.

14:15.318 --> 14:16.552
No.

14:16.553 --> 14:18.387
Now please step away from the baby.

14:18.388 --> 14:20.556
You really freaked me out before.

14:20.557 --> 14:22.791
Yes, sure, of course.

14:22.792 --> 14:26.228
I want to thank everyone for pitching in

14:26.229 --> 14:28.564
and collecting things
we can use as weapons.

14:28.565 --> 14:33.502
But we may need to sort through
and pick out the best bits.

14:33.503 --> 14:35.070
Okay?

14:35.071 --> 14:35.903
Right.

14:37.173 --> 14:40.409
Pots and pans. Very good for bonking heads.

14:40.410 --> 14:43.277
A couple of spatulas, a whisk.

14:44.814 --> 14:47.249
Weren't there any knives in the kitchen?

14:47.250 --> 14:49.485
No? Shame.

14:49.486 --> 14:51.352
I've got a potato. It's very pointy.

14:52.422 --> 14:54.056
I didn't find any weapons,

14:54.057 --> 14:55.724
but I'm really going
to give those Valencians

14:55.725 --> 14:56.959
a piece of my mind.

14:56.960 --> 14:59.395
Her words can be very cutting.

14:59.396 --> 15:02.164
Well, we don't have much
in the way as weapons.

15:02.165 --> 15:05.167
But, uh, we got grit.

15:05.168 --> 15:06.334
And determination.

15:07.771 --> 15:09.437
Yah!

15:11.441 --> 15:14.409
I mean, it's a bit desperate, isn't it?

15:16.045 --> 15:18.547
Come on, guys. Show me something.

15:18.548 --> 15:21.049
There must be more than this aimless amble.

15:21.050 --> 15:22.584
You were soldiers once, weren't you?

15:22.585 --> 15:24.453
Don't you remember any of that?

15:24.454 --> 15:25.587
Huh?

15:25.588 --> 15:26.889
All right, raise your weapons.

15:26.890 --> 15:29.224
[Groaning]

15:29.225 --> 15:31.059
Or not.

15:31.060 --> 15:32.694
Maybe you'll respond to danger!

15:32.695 --> 15:33.896
Aah!

15:33.897 --> 15:37.433
[Thud] Oh, for the love of...

15:37.434 --> 15:38.767
I'm gonna fail.

15:38.768 --> 15:40.369
I'm gonna fail.

15:40.370 --> 15:42.204
[Sighs]

15:42.205 --> 15:46.708
And Isabella is gonna die
thinking I don't love her,

15:46.709 --> 15:48.844
which isn't true.

15:48.845 --> 15:52.581
I love her to the very fiber of my being.

15:52.582 --> 15:54.615
And she'll never know.

15:56.619 --> 15:58.887
Aww.

15:58.888 --> 16:02.124
I love her.

16:02.125 --> 16:03.891
Looooove.

16:05.328 --> 16:07.496
I came back from the dead for love.

16:07.497 --> 16:09.264
Does love speak to you?

16:09.265 --> 16:11.132
All: Looooove.

16:12.202 --> 16:13.634
Will you follow me for love?

16:16.272 --> 16:18.140
Will you fight with me for love?

16:18.141 --> 16:19.575
All: Love!

16:19.576 --> 16:21.543
Now, who's with me? For love!

16:21.544 --> 16:23.312
- All: Love!
- Love!

16:23.313 --> 16:24.646
- Love!
- Love!

16:24.647 --> 16:25.881
Love!

16:25.882 --> 16:28.150
[Speaking gibbering]

16:28.151 --> 16:29.551
Yes.

16:29.552 --> 16:32.019
Well said, my friend. Well said.

16:38.777 --> 16:42.146
Let's saddle up. It's time for battle.

16:42.147 --> 16:44.248
I am ready for war.

16:44.249 --> 16:47.217
And not just to sit in a comfy
chair and watch up on a hill

16:47.218 --> 16:48.452
while eating cucumber sandwiches,

16:48.453 --> 16:50.687
although that was delightful.

16:50.688 --> 16:54.339
No, I am actually ready to
stand next to you and fight.

16:54.359 --> 16:56.226
Sounds like you found
your manhood, Richard.

16:56.227 --> 16:59.229
Bobby found it... A bunch of times,

16:59.230 --> 17:00.397
if you know what I'm saying, huh?

17:00.398 --> 17:02.232
Unfortunately, I do.

17:02.233 --> 17:03.600
Ow. [Inhales sharply]

17:03.601 --> 17:05.868
That's really thick armor.

17:05.869 --> 17:07.171
Has anyone seen Sid?

17:07.172 --> 17:10.273
There's this one strap on
my armor I can never get.

17:10.275 --> 17:11.407
Oh, sorry.

17:11.409 --> 17:14.644
He asked me to give you this last night.

17:19.017 --> 17:21.617
"I can't stand the shame
of having briefly killed

17:21.618 --> 17:23.721
the greatest hero in the seven realms.

17:23.722 --> 17:26.824
I've left to redeem myself. Sid."

17:26.825 --> 17:28.325
He doesn't need to redeem himself.

17:28.326 --> 17:30.694
I was just giving him
a hard t... Damn it, Gal.

17:30.695 --> 17:33.297
Mother always said she
never knew when I was joking.

17:33.298 --> 17:35.032
Oh, I hate it when mother is right.

17:35.033 --> 17:36.432
I'm gonna go find him.

17:40.004 --> 17:42.940
Strange being in this room again.

17:42.941 --> 17:45.743
It seems like a lifetime
ago I sat on that throne.

17:45.744 --> 17:48.311
So much has changed.

17:50.482 --> 17:54.413
Ah, if I ever got the chance to be a king
again, I would do things so differently.

17:57.322 --> 17:59.690
Richard, I have to tell you something.

17:59.691 --> 18:00.657
- Hmm?
- [Clears throat]

18:00.658 --> 18:01.592
Um...

18:01.593 --> 18:05.629
It's hard to say, but, um...

18:05.630 --> 18:08.132
I can't go into battle with you.

18:08.133 --> 18:10.300
What are you talking about?

18:10.301 --> 18:12.102
Richard, you're not a fighter,

18:12.103 --> 18:14.772
and I love you too much to watch you die.

18:14.773 --> 18:17.708
And...You will die.

18:17.709 --> 18:19.076
Horribly.

18:19.077 --> 18:21.078
Mutilated.

18:21.079 --> 18:22.813
- Crying blood.
- [Scoffs] Okay.

18:22.814 --> 18:23.947
Having soiled yourself

18:23.948 --> 18:25.783
with people trying to cut off your head.

18:25.784 --> 18:28.218
People pointing and laughing,

18:28.219 --> 18:30.120
gloating on the battlefield.

18:30.121 --> 18:31.889
- It's gonna be hideous.
- Okay.

18:31.890 --> 18:34.057
- It can be quite fun, but not for you.
- Got it.

18:34.058 --> 18:36.059
I can't be part of that.

18:36.060 --> 18:37.327
It'll destroy me.

18:37.328 --> 18:41.198
My darling, you worry
too much. I'll be fine.

18:41.199 --> 18:44.401
Yes, perhaps a bit less confident

18:44.402 --> 18:47.237
after your very charmingly
graphic description,

18:47.238 --> 18:49.373
but believe me, I'll be fine.

18:49.374 --> 18:52.009
Let's forget this whole battle and leave

18:52.010 --> 18:54.578
and go and build a life for ourselves.

18:54.579 --> 18:57.881
My aunt has a farm across the lonely sea,

18:57.882 --> 18:59.583
in the shadow of mount spinster.

18:59.584 --> 19:01.919
It's so beautiful. Lots of cats.

19:01.920 --> 19:04.521
We can be happy there.

19:04.522 --> 19:07.390
- I can get us one-way tickets, and...
- Bobby.

19:09.060 --> 19:10.994
I have to do this.

19:10.995 --> 19:12.428
I can't let Galavant down.

19:14.132 --> 19:15.631
And I can't watch you die.

19:20.271 --> 19:21.537
So, what are we saying?

19:24.676 --> 19:26.876
I think we're saying goodbye.

